{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-project-jsx","path":"/projects/musish/","result":{"data":{"post":{"html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 750px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/aa601cd196a9ab7c8306006aa3232d07/5e17e/musish.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 70.2127659574468%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Musi.sh\"\n        title=\"Musi.sh\"\n        src=\"/static/aa601cd196a9ab7c8306006aa3232d07/1d69c/musish.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/aa601cd196a9ab7c8306006aa3232d07/4dcb9/musish.png 188w,\n/static/aa601cd196a9ab7c8306006aa3232d07/5ff7e/musish.png 375w,\n/static/aa601cd196a9ab7c8306006aa3232d07/1d69c/musish.png 750w,\n/static/aa601cd196a9ab7c8306006aa3232d07/78797/musish.png 1125w,\n/static/aa601cd196a9ab7c8306006aa3232d07/aa440/musish.png 1500w,\n/static/aa601cd196a9ab7c8306006aa3232d07/5e17e/musish.png 2668w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://img.shields.io/github/stars/Musish/Musish.svg?style=social\" alt=\"Github Stars\"></p>\n<p>On December 1st 2018, a group of friends and I attended the MLH Local Hack Day in San Francisco.</p>\n<p>Made by <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://jamesjarvis.io\" title=\"myself\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">myself</a>, <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://brychan.io\" title=\"Brychan\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">Brychan</a>, <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://raphaelvigee.com\" title=\"Raphaël\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">Raphaël</a>, and <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/filip-grebowski-b24810116/\" title=\"Filip\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">Filip</a>.</p>\n<p>This particular hackathon was sponsored by GitHub and Microsoft, and had a theme of creating the best open source project for the community. We came first in San Francisco for our project.</p>\n<p>We decided to make an <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://musi.sh\" title=\"Apple Music web player\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">Apple Music web player</a>, since pretty much every single other music streaming platform already had one. Some people aren't sure why Apple Music would need a web player, since surely you could just use iTunes for that?</p>\n<p>Well, as was <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://forums.macrumors.com/threads/apple-music-gets-another-unofficial-web-player-with-launch-of-musish.2166187/#post-27018681\" title=\"hilariously summarised in a comment on Macrumors\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">hilariously summarised in a comment on Macrumors</a>, iTunes isn't exactly lightweight.</p>\n<!-- ![iTunes competitor](./iTunesCompetitor.GIF) -->\n<p>Musi.sh (Musish) is an open source project now, using the A-GPL license, and as of February 2019, has over <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://github.com/Musish/Musish/stargazers\" title=\"1400 stars\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">1400 stars</a>, and <a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://github.com/Musish/Musish/graphs/contributors\" title=\"9 contributors\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">9 contributors</a>.</p>\n<p>We released it (sent out a few emails) while walking around Central Park, NY on the 18th January 2019. We weren't really prepared with what was to come, and have since had quite a few articles written about it.</p>\n<h2>Analytics and Feedback</h2>\n<p>According to Google Analytics, we have had over 50,000 unique users on Musi.sh from over 110 different countries, and we have found some very positive articles written about it at least 13 different languages found so far.</p>\n<p>Some notable mentions:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://www.businessinsider.com/uk-tech-100-2019-most-important-interesting-and-impactful-people-uk-tech-2019-9?r=US&IR=T#97-the-undergraduate-students-who-beat-apple-to-building-a-web-player-for-apple-music-4\" title=\"Business Insider Tech 100 2019 #97\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">Business Insider Tech 100 2019 #97</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20200322103909/https://www.kent.ac.uk/\" title=\"University of Kent homepage\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">University of Kent homepage</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20200322104018/https://www.kent.ac.uk/courses/profiles/undergraduate/computer-science-year-industry-musish\" title=\"University of Kent profile\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">University of Kent profile</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://9to5mac.com/2019/01/18/apple-music-web/\" title=\"9to5Mac\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">9to5Mac</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://9to5mac.com/2019/01/21/apple-music-mac-app/\" title=\"9to5Mac again\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">9to5Mac again</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://gizmodo.com/how-to-play-apple-music-from-the-web-1831977569\" title=\"Gizmodo\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">Gizmodo</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://www.macrumors.com/2019/01/21/apple-music-web-player-musish/\" title=\"Macrumors\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">Macrumors</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://www.cultofmac.com/601520/musish-apple-music-web-portal/\" title=\"Cult of Mac\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">Cult of Mac</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://thenextweb.com/apps/2019/01/22/use-apple-music-in-your-browser-with-this-pretty-web-interface/\" title=\"The Next Web\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">The Next Web</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://www.01net.com/actualites/musi-sh-le-service-qui-donne-acces-a-apple-music-depuis-un-navigateur-web-1617352.html#xtor=AL-123461\" title=\"01Net (France)\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">01Net (France)</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://myapple.pl/posts/18640-kolejny-web-player-apple-music-musish-stawia-na-podobienstwo-do-pierwowzoru\" title=\"My Apple (Poland)\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">My Apple (Poland)</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"siteLink\" href=\"https://twitter.com/search?q=Musi.sh\" title=\"Twitter\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow noreferrer\">Twitter</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Also, we made it to #1 and #2 on GitHub trending for all JavaScript projects and all languages respectively on the 19th January 2019, which was our favourite achievement of all!</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 750px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/799d45b0319c406c2b9a2734cdf84783/97806/javascript_trending.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 68.61702127659575%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: bloc